-- Weir Group drops BAML as broker citing conflict of interest
-- By Karolin Schaps
-- Mon Aug 04, 2014 02:37AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Aug 4 (Reuters) - Weir Group <WEIR.L> has terminated its corporate broker agreement with Bank of America Merrill Lynch <BAC.N> after the bank's appointment by another company created a conflict of interest, the British engineering firm said.

"The Weir Group has terminated its joint corporate broker engagement with Bank of America Merrill Lynch," the group said in a statement. Weir said that it would continue with its corporate broker agreement with UBS <UBSN.VX> and would make a further announcement regarding future broker contracts.